{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FGgCrYW79w935Cp6JBRJhZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# metrics\n2\t\n3\tPurpose: HTTP ingestion service that records frontend user interaction events in memory and exposes them for retrieval. Listens on port 8081.\n4\t\n5\tTags: architecture, overview\n6\t\n7\t## Overview\n8\t\n9\tThe metrics composite provides a single `http.Handler` (returned by `New()`) that wires an in-memory event store and an HTTP handler layer together onto one `ServeMux`. The only routes exposed are `POST /events` and `GET /events`.\n10\t\n11\t## Components\n12\t\n13\t| Component | Responsibility |\n14\t|-----------|----------------|\n15\t| [`handlers/`](handlers/README.md) | HTTP layer — decodes requests, enforces the event-type allowlist, delegates storage to a `store.Storer` |\n16\t| [`store/`](store/README.md) | Data-access layer — owns the `Event` type, `Storer` interface, and thread-safe in-memory storage |\n17\t| [`metrics.go`](metrics.go.md) | Package-level wiring — constructs store and handlers, registers routes, returns the composed `http.Handler` |\n18\t\n19\t## Synthesis Docs\n20\t\n21\t- [data-flow.md](data-flow.md) — startup wiring diagram and request-time paths for POST and GET\n22\t\n23\t## API Contract\n24\t\n25\t```\n26\tPOST /events\n27\t  Request:  {\"type\":\"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\",\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}\n28\t  Response: 201 {\"id\":string,\"type\":string,\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}\n29\t  Errors:   400 on invalid JSON or unknown type\n30\t\n31\tGET /events\n32\t  Response: 200 [{\"id\":string,\"type\":string,\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}]\n33\t            200 [] when no events have been recorded\n34\t```\n35\t\n36\t## Data Model\n37\t\n38\t```go\n39\ttype Event struct {\n40\t    ID      string                 `json:\"id\"`\n41\t    Type    string                 `json:\"type\"`\n42\t    UserID  string                 `json:\"userId\"`\n43\t    Payload map[string]interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n44\t}\n45\t```\n46\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a88bef8-124f-476a-a1be-df81e4d77fbe","uuid":"0bc17b10-4de7-4392-bd8e-46bbb22d0f73","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:37:24.152Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/README.md","content":"# metrics\n\nPurpose: HTTP ingestion service that records frontend user interaction events in memory and exposes them for retrieval. Listens on port 8081.\n\nTags: architecture, overview\n\n## Overview\n\nThe metrics composite provides a single `http.Handler` (returned by `New()`) that wires an in-memory event store and an HTTP handler layer together onto one `ServeMux`. The only routes exposed are `POST /events` and `GET /events`.\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------------|\n| [`handlers/`](handlers/README.md) | HTTP layer — decodes requests, enforces the event-type allowlist, delegates storage to a `store.Storer` |\n| [`store/`](store/README.md) | Data-access layer — owns the `Event` type, `Storer` interface, and thread-safe in-memory storage |\n| [`metrics.go`](metrics.go.md) | Package-level wiring — constructs store and handlers, registers routes, returns the composed `http.Handler` |\n\n## Synthesis Docs\n\n- [data-flow.md](data-flow.md) — startup wiring diagram and request-time paths for POST and GET\n\n## API Contract\n\n```\nPOST /events\n  Request:  {\"type\":\"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\",\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}\n  Response: 201 {\"id\":string,\"type\":string,\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}\n  Errors:   400 on invalid JSON or unknown type\n\nGET /events\n  Response: 200 [{\"id\":string,\"type\":string,\"userId\":string,\"payload\":{}}]\n            200 [] when no events have been recorded\n```\n\n## Data Model\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    ID      string                 `json:\"id\"`\n    Type    string                 `json:\"type\"`\n    UserID  string                 `json:\"userId\"`\n    Payload map[string]interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n}\n```\n","numLines":46,"startLine":1,"totalLines":46}}}
